channel.name: three-little-pigs-challenge
channel.topic:
Build 3 different houses: 1 should include hay bales, 1 should include wood planks, 1 should include bricks. Your house with bricks should look strong enough to withstand the big bad wolf’s huffing and puffing! Populate your houses with your 3 favorite pig mob variants! 
Challenge dates: June 16 – June 29 @ 6 PM PDT

messages.content:
:mc_wolf: : Little pig! Little pig! Let me in! Let me in!
:mc_pig: : Not by the hairs on my chinny chin chin!

Oink. It’s the #three-little-pigs-challenge! 
Build three different houses crafted from different materials: one should *include* hay bales, one should *include* wood planks, one should *include* bricks. Your house with bricks should look strong enough to withstand the big bad wolf’s huffing and puffing! Don’t forget to populate your houses with your three favorite pig mob variants (there’s plenty to choose from)! :spotted_pig:

:timer: Challenge dates: June 16 – June 29 @ 6 PM PDT

__Challenge Guidelines__
:earth: Your creation must be built entirely by you and in Minecraft Earth.
:crafting_table: Your build must be a brand new creation, crafted just for this challenge.
:buildplate: Build your imagination! Challenge theme is open to interpretation and buildplate size won’t be a factor in judging.
:sign: Post your images or video submission and buildplate share link in #three-little-pigs-challenge  by the deadline. Feel free to ask a Moderator to pin it!
:challenges: Winning submissions may be used in social media posts.
:fast_parrot: Have fun!

@clovepod  :make_stuff:

Three little pigs,
In the market for housing,
Found a new home
After minutes of browsing.

The land was quite cheap,
Which counts for a lot
When three dollars fifty
Was all that they'd got.

With work to be done,
They each claimed their corner
(For the land had been sold
With the following warner:

*"We suggest that you don't
Try to meet your new neighbours -
They collect cut-throat razors,
Stilettos, and sabres..."*)

So, avoiding the quadrant
With the spooky black pit,
They laid out the plans
For their own precious bit.

The pigs didn't mind
All the ominous howling,
But weren't all that keen
On the after-hours prowling.

"It's fine," said the piebald,
"Once we've built our new homes
We'll be perfectly safe
From those old bags of bones."

"I'm making mine sturdy,
With block after block
Of everything possible
Made out of rock."

*(We shall call him BRICKS)*

"Sounds charming," said the pale pig,
"Though I just don't see why,
When the key to our safety
Is staying up high."

"Perched up in the scaffold,
Like a fine eagles nest,
My home will undoubtedly
Be the best."

*(This one we'll call STICKS)*

"Such clever ideas,
I could never compete!"
Said the muddiest pig
As he put up his feet.

"My humble abode is just this
And no more -
Some day-beds of hay and
An umbrella of straw."

*(For the sake of convenience, he'll be known as... ERIC...s)*

So the game was on
For Bricks and Sticks,
With devious cunning
And mischievous tricks.

Incursions were rife
On their fellow pigs land -
From roller coaster tracks
To a swimming pool, most grand.

They built and constructed
Until blue in the face,
Each determined to own
The most canine-proof place.

But Erics just smiled,
For he'd spotted a clue
And he knew straight away
What the wolves planned to do.....

*Do you?*
